One person was last night recovered dead from the rubbles of a building that collapsed on Akanbi Crescent, Yaba , Lagos State earlier in the day. The victim is believed to be one of the construction workers in the uncompleted building. He was brought out by operatives of the Lagos State Emergency Management Agency who raced to the scene. The identity of the victim could not be immediately confirmed.   Tax reforms to double Nigeria’s tax to GDP ratio, says CITN     Military school alumni join drug war, support NDLEA     The Nation’s Ololade makes final shortlist for Fetisov…   The number of people trapped in the building could not also be ascertained at press time. - Advertisement - The three-storey building, which was under construction, collapsed into another building beside it. The Nation learnt several construction workers are trapped under the rubbles as at time of the report. Security operatives, Lagos State Emergency Management Agency (LASEMA) and other emergency responders have arrived at the scene for rescue operations. SPONSORED